auri qumque pondo, ‘ five pounds weight of the bullion.’ Pondo is a heteroclite ablative from pondus, which was originally used in construction with librae ε e.g. auri quinque libras pondo, ‘ five pounds in weight (abl. of respect) of bullion.' When librae was dropped out, pondo came to be used as if it were an indeclinable noun.
